reviews.review_text: Sounds like the best we're going to have I've been listening to this concert and the AUD aren't terrible, but this SBD really is better. I think this, or the version also released by Kevin Tobin (the one that can't be played through archive.org natively) will be the best quality for download for free we will ever get of this date. The concert is also one of the best 10 ever played by the band, the Attics makes me remember my deceased grandmother and always makes me tear up a little. Thank you so much for this upload. Downloading right now.

Camped on Bull's Island on the Delaware river My good buddy Mike drove up for the last show of  5 at Meadowlands all three Spectrum shows and both Charlotte Show's. We arrived to Bull's Island about 1 am on the 16th to a locked gate ,and tired from the long drive we just went to sleep in the car  GDTS sent flyers with our order of tickets that's how we knew of it and camping in the Venue Parking Lot was banned beginning this tour and Meadowlands Yellow Jackets were more than happy to enforce it ,At the Spectrum in Philly we paid think 20 $ and  slept in the car right there  all three nights. Back tp Bull's Island though, so we woke up in the morning on the 16th around daybreak and the gate was now unlocked and we proceeded to drive in there and there was a couple buildings like a Visitor Center that was closed the whole time and another building that a free laundry mat with a few washers and dryers big restrooms with nice showers . . We were always wary of Park Rangers busting us for smoking pot , but the way they seemed so nice to open the Gate without even waking us up sort of indicated we were safe and we were , the only thing we could have had to make it better would have been some Sugar Magnolias(Girls),We never saw anybody the whole time but two other Guys who got the flyer and they really stuck to themselves and .after one encounter we didn't see them ,so we basically had the whole Island to ourselves and hung out there until about noon and headed for the Meadowlands and maybe an hour later we were there ,The weather was Mostly Sunny with Manhattan easily visible across the water. The Scene outside the Arena was kind of  Bleak  with talk of security wearing riot gear and rough housing clearing the Lot which I experienced myself  when I was Mikes Car and they were coming my direction and there was a guy with VW micro bus that had empty beer bottles all around the wheels in front and back and I heard them be Commanded to get in Vehicle and go now ,and the Guy said can't I pick up these Bottles and I don't know what exactly was said but the guy with the VW was persuaded very Rapidly to get in his van and pull out crushing dozens of bottles beneath his tires . I'm standing there watching in disbelief and they told me to leave to leave ,and I said I"M just waiting for MIke to get back to the car , I was informed if I didn't leave right then They would be authorized to remove me , Luckily Mike walked up right then and they told him the same thing and you knew they meant it and we didn't even know about Adam Katz Murder yet   , and  as we pulled out I heard a couple bottles shatter under  his wheels , Thankfully we got out uninjured with no flat tires . The show Inside we just witnessed had  one of the most innovative ,rare unusual , well played  Second set's of any era not following any similar set  like the familiar common  Space >Other One>Wharf Rat>Throwing Stones > Not Fade away , Brokedown Palace . They were out on a limb in unchartered  territory and it almost seemed like they'd been rehearsing the set it sounded so planned out but you knew it wasn't . I thought the Vocals On " Attics of my Life" were great and I think the Vocals sound better on the Audience tapes , but for the instruments Sound Board , that's what  makes Ultra Matrix so Good the sound of the room the way it sounded coupled  with deep clarity of the a Soundboard  covers the Whole soundscape  . And it's easy to see why this was Officially Released , Not a huge fan of Midi the way Jerry employed it that night was mesmerizing and hypnotic  with a stellar sound of the whole set Dipped in Dark Star with the WOLF guitar sounding classic when it was off MIDI , and when it was on His incredible timing and technique ensured his exquisite sound was Unique  , and Nobody Packing stadiums sounded like him at all in '89 , Very few sound close to him today , and if they could , could they do it different every time too , Making  it sound your tying Ribbon around some sweet licks that you just Dealt out  like a card dealer . I heard   create senses of movement 
 Flipping through and cutting the whole deck   I have never seen anybody really fulfil Jerry's role , Players that might be technically better still just don't seem to do it as mystical as Jerry . We got back to Bull's earlier than expected as fast as they cleared the lot and were  on cloud 9 , and I don't remember going to sleep , and spent the Day off on the 17th exploring the Island  having guitar Jams in the laundry room while it poured rain off and on. My vision of New Jersey was the Jersey Shore or Newark , and was happy to camp out in such beautiful Country side ,and I understood what they were talking about when I would see "Garden State" on the License plates , It seemed like when we crossed into Pennsylvania  it was always grey and cloudy I think the Sun finally came out in the afternoon on the last night at Philly  however brief it didn't surprise me when we got a nice "Fire On The Mountain" even though jerry Flubbed the words like he didn't even know the song , while his guitar playing behind that was excellent
